phrases.catch: I caught a walker cicada! Pffft... I walk all the time and no one calls me "Walker ..."
phrases.blathers: The walker cicada is quite the noisy thing. I tell you, this impolite pest simply canNOT abide the quiet. In the heat of summer, the male strikes up a strange rattling song, hoping to woo a mate. When other male cicadas hear this rhythmic racket, they join right in... As if it were a sing-along! My head aches at the thought of it.
